<h2><a href="http://slehar.com/wwwRel//cartoonepist/cartoonepist1.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Part I: Something Very Strange!</a></h2>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-23.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/PRU7OY6g0F3sZ09xqOST4BOkWQj3Y42FJWT97wsgYnk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yMy5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMyMCUyQzIyNiZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" width="320" height="226" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Ij4xmrPPiK0VjaVPH6cSU9mQKzs24OAI_dj2F_qAnQw=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yMy5wbmc_dz0zMjAmc3NsPTE= 320w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Fx9kIPHnLcWcsXCvd33k20gMd43HtamrfeMX4tOQSkc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yMy5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIxMiZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Did you ever notice? There is something ver-ry strange about this world of ours.</p>



<p><em>Really? Like what?</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-24.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="311" height="230" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/H05jtXf7rdsXcX36kKARZa2_g0S1LC8Aksm1ue73VlU=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMxMSUyQzIzMCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/V7ERPzDR_gaN7coZepu4y4t6PiGNe_A0wPG7oXLEBCQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNC5wbmc_dz0zMTEmc3NsPTE= 311w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Gr3XF-zqZ5JOdazjkXY-4ouKB9ZLqYWkc9fS6C7lisQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIyMiZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Do you ever feel like you are trapped in some kind of bubble? I mean look—the sky looks like a dome over my head. Is that really the shape of the sky? And did you notice something really funny?</p>



<p><em>No what? Tell me!</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-25.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="320" height="220" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/WT_MPdaNc8Az9whQXZ80QlqD-7cByj-5ZH2p4_J6CS0=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMyMCUyQzIyMCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/LFvFg19pFDbOYYdLmOK-y9J3wf1qaFx03FXi-e77CVg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNS5wbmc_dz0zMjAmc3NsPTE= 320w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/aZiHf8ry1fTlxr3fd2DEa8-UzzvHM6eZYn8Ihu9NJBs=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIwNiZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Did you ever notice that things that are far away look smaller? And things that are nearby look bigger! Do you realize how strange that is?</p>



<p><em>Strange? That’s not strange at all! Thats just perspective, just like it happens in a camera. In a photograph farther things look smaller, too.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-26.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="496" height="200" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/taeDCSgVJ2X-yXatfyvUIo0wrtR2okggsIIJWrT7FKc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNi5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTQ5NiUyQzIwMCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Wt9jeylb_0zBZd45h_sp4zEPs4eiNRYMokp5Ddh8AK8=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNi5wbmc_dz00OTYmc3NsPTE= 496w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/cAK205cOw3B75qz7X44JPN9zfA1fb5XobraaIAepx-w=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNi5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzEyMSZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Yes, but the perspective in a camera is projected onto the flat sheet of film. There is no mystery in that kind of perspective, it is simply a projection from a 3-D world through a focal point onto a 2-D surface. And in your eyeball the retina is like the film.</p>



<p><em>So?</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-27.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="320" height="233" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/OLArkyZQ-EavTw_xH5dAgxsRIzmvj4MIZeovePfwkQk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNy5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMyMCUyQzIzMyZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/By1reVh4-qQ6ZEV3yvZPtZQ9zPTTStdWDgNdH_D9O3s=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNy5wbmc_dz0zMjAmc3NsPTE= 320w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/k3N-_hUDyYR3qy7CjDGB7aoxt2Jl4Y8eYBUWD36ZgKo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yNy5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIxOCZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>But take a look at this street here. Is this street the picture on your retina?</p>



<p><em>No, that’s the street itself where the light comes from that makes the image on my retina.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-28.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="420" height="178" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/5mq75vdGXZyykdkMQVKtlbzZdPhVDoYt3tPK7GR6Gyo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yOC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTQyMCUyQzE3OCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/FAL1KQBY8lhhmLYmutybhlpfJq3JgYiN6y5fJYhhQQU=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yOC5wbmc_dz00MjAmc3NsPTE= 420w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/81K4bIDcpNt1Kmqv1qKSb0xHL2pJDu-mD0VTZka1g_E=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yOC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzEyNyZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>But then how come things in the distance look smaller? Perspective is something that happens in your eye, not out in the world! In the real street things in the distance are not actually smaller, all the houses are exactly the same size. It is only on your retina that the farther ones appear smaller. And the image on your retina is only a flat 2-D image. This world out here is 3-D, but it has perspective. So is it the world itself? Or is it the image on the retina?</p>



<p><em>Well, it’s both. Light from the world makes a picture in your eye that lets you see the things out in the world. What’s so hard about that?</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-29.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="308" height="287" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/vKq5DWed8PaaJp94mg8V8KTlIZsakOuiCUu6sYBehG0=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yOS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwOCUyQzI4NyZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/QNbdyNMnHGmXM_Sdvh0Q5VMGdPuQTRM4oLu0qR7PSPg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yOS5wbmc_dz0zMDgmc3NsPTE= 308w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/TLF6V5rAoZj-CuUXc60ApJlQ3Mb2PMIbKIYC7K4H0Ik=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0yOS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzI4MCZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 308px) 100vw, 308px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Ok then if this is the world itself, then why is everything bent around like a reflection in a Christmas bulb?</p>



<p><em>I don’t see anything bent. What are you talking about?</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-30.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="320" height="283" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/25B_Uw7lENP-CpSTX1WXvYFHlk5uQswFPKiOX4zS_RY=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMyMCUyQzI4MyZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/2nGg00feZrRJ77MuZI6tXgSaS3CbqP57KbBp8MnfB3Q=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMC5wbmc_dz0zMjAmc3NsPTE= 320w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/WXXjRU7cnvEzbwTGB-lxO6B-AHDhdzgsG1E6nQvRRS4=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzI2NSZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Well, take a look at this. See the two sides of this street? They are straight and parallel as far as the eye can see.</p>



<p><em>So?</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-31.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/XbYcUQO8RFfxpm6A4fyTkL6pKbWruHEXpmli_T23x9Y=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMyMCUyQzI0OSZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" width="320" height="249" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ro27dWf9zoZD5O1H1cD0Ya4iNKdaCqumzQzaSmW4DWc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMS5wbmc_dz0zMjAmc3NsPTE= 320w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/3lyKLt30UKdZ1MfiP7eoPpawU7N4afBu7W5xXMmn078=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIzMyZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>But LOOK! Those straight parallel sides also MEET AT A POINT! RIGHT THERE! Can you SEE it?</p>



<p><em>Well they LOOK like they meet at a point. But they don’t really!</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-32.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="320" height="291" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/6NqRd6Rv3_WDruKOzYUR8BDsJE7PvEVSUGvjGUv9tsc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMi5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMyMCUyQzI5MSZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/AWkC66D0WmZZ-UjANVUWWJHVO7iBAYrnJcxgOK5IBUE=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMi5wbmc_dz0zMjAmc3NsPTE= 320w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/X8kgiDyybmOR1rsebBs64E74M2cizrHv9WAC3Uiyd1g=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMi5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzI3MyZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>And if you turn around and look behind you, they meet at a point back there too!</p>



<p><em>So? I don’t get it.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-33.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="245" height="158" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/sw9TprwPZsp-y5vQKSSMNDxECVY1MzOp_UMZ_WtnROk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS0zMy5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTI0NSUyQzE1OCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>So this street that we are standing on is shaped like the rind of a melon slice with two curved sides that meet at a point at either end. And those end points are at eye level, even though the street is under our feet.</p>



<p><em>Ok, vision is not perfect. So what?</em></p>



