<p></p>



<p>Ok, then <strong><em>you</em></strong> tell me. How does vision work?</p>



<p><em>Well, first of all, this here is the real world, not some kind of image in anybody’s head. And there is nothing bent or bulgy about it, the world is perfectly straight! The sides of the road don’t converge, they only seem to converge. And they never do actually meet, if you look very carefully. And farther things are not really smaller, they only appear to be smaller. It’s an illusion.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-48.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="256" height="185" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/BrWVPUK_uMvaktSdqkutkSLSIfnrnemz5RpNmEWOrD4=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS00OC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTI1NiUyQzE4NSZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p><em>Now light from the world enters your eye where it makes an image on your retina. The retina sends an electrical signal up the optic nerve that generates electrical activation in the visual cortex.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-49.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="320" height="238" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/FUCKKOw6T_dJGn5QZl7J8zsfPmMPSwAWnXAYH09L6VM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS00OS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMyMCUyQzIzOCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/wVry-PtFBBg3vwZESM86eHIrCPgn53mY7SUlW4t0K_E=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS00OS5wbmc_dz0zMjAmc3NsPTE= 320w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/E8uEv5yVKVU31tvUA8akncaFejMhQD7IJRU_kPNViE0=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS00OS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIyMyZzc2w9MQ== 300w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/HDc2jTZDE2U50D5ukaI-SBkDQLzxTYiguXMw1PaApog=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS00OS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTIwMCUyQzE1MCZzc2w9MQ== 200w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p><em>And as the cortex lights up electrically, you see the world around you.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-50.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="384" height="238" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Hz8Qu4kHZV4SrjBUGStBcEWdTKYLbYc2LzrjSgsUt1I=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01MC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NCUyQzIzOCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/aVgic_32WTiI6YrvOyx0eqnZyF9BPx7JeteClIKmhN0=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01MC5wbmc_dz0zODQmc3NsPTE= 384w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/CUoue-Ivi5DIWfIdo1WRDM9hC2hkBCWmZ0tgtVgsFIk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01MC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzE4NiZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Is the electrical activity in the cortex shaped like a street with houses under a domed sky?</p>



<p><em>No! Neurons chatter away in the brain in a pattern that is nothing like the shape of the world you see.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-51.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="385" height="204" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/fqtcd-tc2cgLHA7a99Z-QTUAaN1FhLLzzFJf0zsMmFg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01MS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NSUyQzIwNCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/t0PXfhv1l2yMCIwVdhztXabtK-2ZCqalCpy4HZsZzT4=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01MS5wbmc_dz0zODUmc3NsPTE= 385w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/N007z9flDPflGvqQPvgGxOMn63fNgyQu3FbXQ5FGS5M=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01MS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzE1OSZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 385px) 100vw, 385px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>Then where does the shape of visual experience come from? Where is the picture that we see?</p>



<p><em><strong>The world</strong>! It comes from <strong>the world</strong>! The shapes and colors you see around you are shapes and colors of the world, not patterns in your brain!</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-52.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="384" height="238" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/DcEU_qKh12jw0OEDn8EhizdUqMNqBE-ofBkv2icWSkQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01Mi5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NCUyQzIzOCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/tGUaGrkJRAbtiBncrCONawMEcICX_IR8les_CRv1Q54=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01Mi5wbmc_dz0zODQmc3NsPTE= 384w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ONIKYQTE6O2FDtHLYTmI2xUWHX8N7HJ9iGK932Uc7hY=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01Mi5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzE4NiZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>But what if you are having a lucid dream, or a hallucination? Then you are seeing shapes and colors that are not in the world. Where are the shapes and colors of the hallucinated scene?</p>



<p><em>They’re in your head of course! But in your head they do not have the shapes and colors you see. In your brain they are just a bunch of neurons chattering to each other.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-53.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="256" height="204" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/4mhOucPs1i2-XtB8w9fUVbDLwrjuhnIGgQ3QIHqL3Uw=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01My5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTI1NiUyQzIwNCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>But then where do the shapes and colors you see come from? Why don’t you just see the shapes of the neurons and their activations? What is it that turns the patterns of electrical activity into the patterns that we experience?</p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-54.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="384" height="256" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/0HZ9RBycOTLumqwQcrIgn3LB-mhiOZdQzOTkR8ldSoM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01NC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NCUyQzI1NiZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/bWQ1-UPLKqkOd33DCl0Q08iHiGY26v0ojR-GoTZ28Pg=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01NC5wbmc_dz0zODQmc3NsPTE= 384w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/7mf9irwT_o-kNS-e296i3aeygYwH5RfuJD0V6wENWcM=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01NC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIwMCZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p><em>The pattern of electrical activation in your brain during a hallucination takes the same shape as it would during a normal perception of the hallucinated scene. So the shape and color that you experience are the shape and color that the world would have if you were perceiving it instead of hallucinating it. They are the shape and color of the <strong>world,</strong> not of your brain! <strong>Even if that world is imaginary!</strong></em></p>



<p>But then what determines which neurons, or patterns of activity, represent which experienced shapes? What is the mapping between the shape of the neurons, or patterns of activation, and the shapes that we experience?</p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-55.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="256" height="141" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/y7RDTgHIAhTS_BrNpXQffw67SmlzJ8S0x0CewcQujKw=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01NS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTI1NiUyQzE0MSZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p><em>The mapping is learned from experience! One neuron, or neuron assembly, learns to fire whenever you see a house, while other neurons, or assemblies, learn to respond to windows, doors, and roofs, for example. The collective pattern of activation of all of these neurons together corresponds to our experience of the external scene.</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-56.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="256" height="137" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/zwWfgbmJK__sqV3u0zBwQzcAVrWcMUCyWKzml-2Vt80=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01Ni5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTI1NiUyQzEzNyZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p><em>And in dreams and hallucinations, the same constellation of neural activations produces the same kind of visual experience as a perception of the corresponding real scene!</em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-57.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="385" height="213" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/86xRPUchgZ9iYmXD0pSpYLOM90G5XrUa0yHIVIYpkuI=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01Ny5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NSUyQzIxMyZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/yEmTPejC32kHflTZC2zks34HTvQ-jBuSle0KJBCgJhs=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01Ny5wbmc_dz0zODUmc3NsPTE= 385w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/-3UQv-ztD6EY5xU1Qi07k2LMfujwbRHMZ01efqvwbFk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01Ny5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzE2NiZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 385px) 100vw, 385px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>But where is this experience located? We can see quite plainly that it is a spatial structure. But where is that structure? What is it made of and where is it located?</p>



<p><em>It’s <strong>out in the WORLD of course</strong>! Experience is right out here in the world where we observe the world to be!</em></p>



<p></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-58.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="384" height="241" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/rHByVoVpPYwYG1nP_pomzxLzWQZ59Pvwj5FT9895LLY=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01OC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NCUyQzI0MSZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/7ahDqUS3t8qAWjaPbd-qZ9Zys3WkZ9snWDsryVNjNmc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01OC5wbmc_dz0zODQmc3NsPTE= 384w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/UZQNfz5SL1YVlUFAZHCiQ-qg2bbW-8IEMjO3NkSRusE=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS01OC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzE4OCZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p>So, let me get this straight. Experience is a spatial structure, as we can plainly see. And your experience occurs as the result of some kind of activation in your brain. But your experience is not in the brain, it is out in the world, although it is caused by electrical events in your physical brain.</p>



<p><em>Yeah, thats right!</em></p>



<figure><img srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/sVzDa-3Qif04Uqz1beCXFbZy1afMfhWuIQfJhfF8kFY=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMS53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9GaWczM0EuanBlZz9zdHJpcD1pbmZvJnc9NDAwJnNzbD0x 400w" alt="" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/C4p2BesMmJUyRTWyuwB0fSO5RmC--gIy71AlCGKUPm4=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMS53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9GaWczM0EuanBlZz9zc2w9MQ==" loading="lazy"/></figure><figure><img srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/LNvNHZm1VKia9vs-w7TegfoLsX6vQC3OOKrbc9XynIk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMi53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9GaWczM0IuanBlZz9zdHJpcD1pbmZvJnc9NDAwJnNzbD0x 400w" alt="" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/M50zMSqd_f-5s5eVNf8Qw1N-PoY-xgObdTyqsy1UVZ0=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMi53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9GaWczM0IuanBlZz9zc2w9MQ==" loading="lazy"/></figure>



<p></p>



<p>So let’s say I had a switch that could turn your brain on and off like a light bulb. Are you telling me that every time I turned it on, the experience would appear out there, but when I turn it off, then the experience disappears? Is experience like a beam of light from a flashlight that is projected outward from the brain? What is that experience made of? What is its substance?</p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-60.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="384" height="334" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/OO-_fnL_4yu_0XxD3ADfusz2aIY9OOpWtzkU33gDoEk=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS02MC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NCUyQzMzNCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/u9KUr_nt8otdiuvwkGTONryzSR2lOsZHZ_C2ZFUEwUc=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS02MC5wbmc_dz0zODQmc3NsPTE= 384w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/UwUlPUQMaM96Xbck0pajvXsjoW_7_jGRgVibZPQb-j4=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS02MC5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzI2MSZzc2w9MQ== 300w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p><em><strong>Its not made of ANYTHING! It is just EXPERIENCE! It doesn’t really EXIST in a physical sense! Nothing is actually projected, it is only EXPERIENCED to be projected!</strong></em></p>



<figure><a href="https://i0.wp.com/qualiacomputing.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-61.png?ssl=1" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><img width="384" height="288" src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/2hJWavTgFGI5OPmcS2OcP_8zEx_uvdFmFToMy2NLZgo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS02MS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTM4NCUyQzI4OCZzc2w9MQ==" alt="" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/Y6Se95HAA9KxlzPeJrxO3qoP4YS95kC58hnnMl9oyOQ=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS02MS5wbmc_dz0zODQmc3NsPTE= 384w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/XM9AU7JZiOdrPFVTGJ0ffFc6VQM-1QazNxUlD-okfHs=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS02MS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTMwMCUyQzIyNSZzc2w9MQ== 300w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/lkGV0B_Q_I0nLwNHiRC__9uaHvoeqcVTCwCOtogSx8E=/aHR0cHM6Ly9pMC53cC5jb20vcXVhbGlhY29tcHV0aW5nLmNvbS93cC1jb250ZW50L3VwbG9hZHMvMjAyMi8xMi9pbWFnZS02MS5wbmc_cmVzaXplPTIwMCUyQzE1MCZzc2w9MQ== 200w" sizes="(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px" loading="lazy"/></a></figure>


<p></p>



<p><strong>Doesn’t exist? This here? The fabric of experience? Doesn’t exist??? All this here is really a bunch of scrambled neurons firing in my brain? I don’t care what you say, I see a spatial structure in experience, and if I see it, I know that it exists!</strong></p>







<h2><a href="http://slehar.com/wwwRel//cartoonepist/cartoonepistP3.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Part III: It’s all in your head!</a></h2>



